place.name: FRITTENDEN
place.gazetteerText: FRITTENDEN, a village and a parish in Cranbrook district, Kent. The village stands 3 miles SE of Staplehurst r. station, and 4 NNE of Cranbrook; and it has a post office under Staplehurst. The parish comprises 3, 318 acres. Real property, £4, 105. Pop., 898. Houses, 176. The property is much subdivided. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Canterbury. Value, £287.* Patron, the Rev. Edward Moore. The church is modern. There are a national school, and charities £51. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
